title: Football Top 10: Red Bank Regional moves up
text:
MORE Red Bank Regional keeps proving the skeptics wrong.
And as a result, the Bucs, who are 6-0 for the first time in years and have clinched a tie for their Shore Conference divisional championship since 1977 keep moving up in the Asbury Park Press Football Top 10.
Red Bank's come-from-behind 24-21 win over Red Bank Catholic â€” last week's No. 3 ranked team, enables it to move up four spots to No. 4 in this week's Top 10.
It was the third time this season Red Bank has defeated a team that was ranked at the time it played that team. The Bucs defeated Ocean (5-1) on Sept. 25 at a time the Spartans were ranked No. 8. They defeated Raritan (3-2) on Oct. 9 at a time the Rockets were ranked No. 10.
